Chocolate Pecan Squares
  --mom (Carol Unmack)

Crust:
1 c flour
1/2 c sugar
1/2 tsp baking soda
1/4 tsp salt
1/4 c butter

Combine clour, sugar. baking soda, and salt in small bowl. Cut in butter with pastry blender until mixture resembles fine crumbs. Press evenly into foil-lined and greases 13x9" baking pan. Bake at 350F for 7 min.


Filling:
2 c chocolate pieces
1 c corn syrup
1/3 c sugar
3 eggs
1 c chopped pecans
1/4 c butter, melted
1/2 tsp salt

Melt chocolate pieces over hot, not boiling, water and set aside. Combine corn syrup, eggs, sugar, butter, and salt. Beat well. Blend into melted chocolate and stir in pecans. Pour pecan filling over warm cookie base. Bake at 350F for 35-40 min. Cool. Then cut into 3" squares. Makes 12.



Notes: This is another of my mom's recipes that I have not altered the instructions for
